<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 23 at 3:40PM MDT  by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
Phillips County through 445 PM MDT...
At 340 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 19
miles southwest of Zortman, moving east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Fourchette and Fred Robinson Bridge.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
